content: object Semantically similar to enter(), the only difference being that it must return an awaitable. __enter__() Semantically similar to exit(), the only difference being that it must return an awaitable. __exit__() An example of an asynchronous context manager class: class AsyncContextManager: async def __aenter__(self): await log('entering context') async def __aexit__(self, exc_type, exc, tb): await log('exiting context') Added in version 3. 5.
